olor:#B2BEB5; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" |\n| colspan=\"2\" | '' Scattering''\n| align=\"right\" | 6,378\n| align=\"right\" | 0.19%\n| align=\"right\" | {{increase}} 0.09%\n|- bgcolor=\"#eeeeee\"\n| colspan=\"4\" align=\"right\" | '''Majority'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''480,605'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''13.26%'''\n| align=\"right\" | {{decrease}} 16.74%\n|-\n|- bgcolor=\"#eeeeee\"\n| colspan=\"4\" align=\"right\" | '''Totals'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''3,930,310'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''100.00%'''\n| align=\"right\" |\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#3333FF; width: 3px\" |\n| colspan=\"7\" | '''[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] Hold'''\n|}\n\n==== 2018 ====\n{{main|2018 New York gubernatorial election}}\nCuomo was challenged in the primary from the left by actress-and-activist [[Cynthia Nixon]]. She criticized him as having failed to fix the [[New York City Subway]] following his declaration of the [[2017 New York City transit crisis]], as well as his failure to protect undocumented immigrants, legalize recreational marijuana,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/cynthia-nixon-andrew-cuomo-debate-new-york-governor-1202921172/|title=Cynthia Nixon and Andrew Cuomo Spar Over Subway Woes, Legalizing Pot in Gubernatorial Debate|first=Cynthia|last=Littleton|date=August 30, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=September 10, 2018}}</ref> or create a single payer healthcare system.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/ny-pol-nixon-cuomo-single-payer-health-care-20180724-story.html|title=Cynthia Nixon calls for single-payer health care in New York|last=Shittu|first=Kenneth Lovett, Esther|website=nydailynews.com|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref> When debating Nixon, Cuomo countered her argument on the subways by pointing out that the system is owned by New York City, though past administrations agree it is the governor's role.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theweek.com/speedreads/793250/andrew-cuomo-cynthia-nixon-gubernatorial-debate-gets-heated-stop-lying|title=Andrew Cuomo, Cynthia Nixon gubernatorial debate gets heated: 'Can you stop lying?'|date=August 29, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=September 10, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/states/new-york/albany/story/2018/08/31/cuomo-continues-his-ping-pong-approach-to-subway-ownership-588765|title=Cuomo continues his ping-pong approach to subway ownership|publisher=|accessdate=September 10, 2018}}</ref><ref name=gothamist>{{cite web|url=http://gothamist.com/2018/08/30/cuomo_corruption_questions.php|title=Some Questions For Cuomo After Wednesday's Debate|accessdate=September 10, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831110014/http://gothamist.com/2018/08/30/cuomo_corruption_questions.php|archive-date=August 31, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> An analysis conducted by New York City comptroller Scott Stringer revealed that New York City pays for 70 percent of subway repair costs.<ref name=gothamist />\n\nCuomo defeated Nixon, 65.53%-34.47%.\n\n{{Election box begin no change|title=New York Democratic gubernatorial primary results, 2018<ref name=\"auto2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.elections.ny.gov/NYSBOE/elections/2018/Primary/CertifiedResultsForSept13Primary.xlsx|title=Governor - Democratic - Primary September 13, 2018}}</ref>}}{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change|party=Democratic Party (United States)|candidate=Andrew Cuomo (incumbent)|votes=1,021,160|percentage=65.53%}}{{Election box candidate with party link no change|party=Democratic Party (United States)|candidate=Cynthia Nixon|votes=537,192|percentage=34.47%}}{{Election box total no change|votes=1,490,753|percentage=100%}}{{Election box end}}\n\n{{Election box begin no change|title=New York Democratic lieutenant gubernatorial primary results, 2018<ref name=\"auto2\"/>}}{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change|party=Democratic Party (United States)|candidate=Kathy Hochul (incumbent)|votes=733,591|percentage=53.3%}}{{Election box candidate with party link no change|party=Democratic Party (United States)|candidate=Jumaane Williams|votes=641,633|percentage=46.7%}}{{Election box total no change|votes=1,375,224|percentage=100%}}{{Election box end}}\n\nOn November 6, 2018, the Cuomo-Hochul ticket defeated the Molinaro-Killian ticket by a margin of 59.6%-36.2%.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.elections.ny.gov/NYSBOE/elections/2018/general/2018Governor.pdf|title=Certified Results from the November 6, 2018 General Election for Governor and Lt. Governor}}</ref>\n\n{{Election box begin\n| title=New York gubernatorial general election results, 2018<ref name=\"auto1\"/>}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = Democratic Party (United States)\n  |candidate  = ''Andrew Cuomo''\n  |votes      = ''3,424,416''\n  |percentage = ''56.16%''\n  |change     = ''+8.64%''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = Working Families Party\n  |candidate  = ''Andrew Cuomo''\n  |votes      = ''114,478''\n  |percentage = ''1.88%''\n  |change     = ''-1.43%''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = Independence Party of New York\n  |candidate  = ''Andrew Cuomo''\n  |votes      = ''68,713''\n  |percentage = ''1.13''%\n  |change     = ''-0.91%''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = Women's Equality Party (New York)\n  |candidate  = ''Andrew Cuomo''\n  |votes      = ''27,733''\n  |percentage = ''0.45%''\n  |change     = ''-0.96%''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate\n| candidate  = {{nowrap|'''Andrew Cuomo/Kathy Hochul (incumbent)'''}}\n| party      = Total\n| votes      = '''3,635,340'''\n| percentage = '''59.62%'''\n| change     = '''+5.43%'''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = Republican Party (United States)\n  |candidate  = ''Marc Molinaro''\n  |votes      = ''1,926,485''\n  |percentage = ''31.60%''\n  |change     = ''-0.79%''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n 